specific functions for this analysis

subMerge <- function(object, sel.dataset){
  if (!all(sel.dataset %in% unique(object$dataset))){
    stop ("Dataset not found in object")
  }

  sel.bcs = names(object$dataset)[object$dataset %in% sel.dataset]

  object@metadata <- object@metadata[sel.bcs, ]

  for (i in c("dataset", "clusters")){
    object@metadata[, i] <- factor(object@metadata[, i])
  }

  object@diff.lrscore <- object@diff.lrscore[, sel.bcs]
  object@cont.lrscore <- object@cont.lrscore[, sel.bcs]

  object@diff.results <- list()
  object@cont.results <- list()

  return(object)
}

load cytosignal object and library size information

data = readRDS("PKdataset.RDS")

Subset the SNCA-OVX mice then run the model.

data_pk = subMerge(data, c(
  "YOUNG_OVX_1", "YOUNG_OVX_2", "YOUNG_OVX_3", "YOUNG_OVX_4",
  "OLD_OVX_1", "OLD_OVX_2", "OLD_OVX_3", "OLD_OVX_4", "OLD_OVX_5"
))
covariates = c("clusters","age")
if ("dataset" %in% covariates) {
        warning("'dataset' will be ignored from covariates.")
        covariates <- covariates[covariates != "dataset"]
    }
    modelsetup <- cytosignal:::.setup.model(data_pk, covariates)
    model.pk <- modelsetup[[1]]

cont.res.pk.all <- nebula(data_pk@cont.lrscore, data_pk$dataset,
pred = model.pk, ncore = 10, verbose = TRUE, offset = data_pk@metadata[["total_counts"]],
cpc = 0.001)
diff.res.pk.all <- nebula(data_pk@diff.lrscore, data_pk$dataset,
pred = model.pk, ncore = 10, verbose = TRUE, offset = data_pk@metadata[["total_counts"]],
cpc =  0.001)

extract regression results

cont.res.pk.all.summary <- cont.res.pk.all$summary
    #cont.res.summary <- cont.res$summary
covlevelmap <- cytosignal:::.covlevelmap(data)
modelcnmap <- stats::setNames(object = paste0(covlevelmap[[1]], 
        "_", covlevelmap[[2]]), nm = paste0(covlevelmap[[1]], 
        covlevelmap[[2]]))
summary.cn <- colnames(cont.res.pk.all.summary)
summary.cn <- summary.cn[!grepl("_\\(Intercept\\)$", summary.cn)]
summary.cn <- summary.cn[!startsWith(summary.cn, "gene")]
covnames <- unique(gsub("^(logFC|se|p)_", "", summary.cn))
summary.cn <- lapply(covnames, function(cov) {
        paste0(c("logFC", "se", "p"), "_", cov)
    })
cont.res.pk.list <- lapply(seq_along(summary.cn), function(i) {
        sub <- cont.res.pk.all.summary[, summary.cn[[i]]]
        colnames(sub) <- c("logFC", "se", "p")
        sub$padj <- stats::p.adjust(sub$p, method = "fdr")
        sub$interaction <- cont.res.pk.all.summary$gene
        sub <- sub[, c(5, 1, 2, 3, 4)]
        rownames(sub) <- NULL
        return(sub)
    })
covnames <- modelcnmap[covnames]
names(cont.res.pk.list) <- covnames
